# Architecture

## Stack
- **Next.js 15** App Router — server components by default, client only when needed
- **Supabase** — PostgreSQL + Auth + RLS + Storage (hosted, project: owvtfzxvirttrbcsiveg)
- **Tailwind CSS v4** — utility-first, mobile-first
- **Vercel** — deployment target (region: cdg1 — Paris, closest to Morocco)

## Folder structure
```
src/
  app/
    (admin)/          # Admin route group — role guard in layout.tsx
    (affiliate)/      # Affiliate route group — role guard in layout.tsx
    (wholesale)/      # Wholesale route group — role guard in layout.tsx
    (auth)/           # Login/signup pages
    actions/          # Server actions (auth.ts, products.ts, orders.ts, cart.ts)
    products/[id]/    # Public product page (COD order form, no auth)
  components/
    admin/            # Admin-only components
    affiliate/        # Affiliate-only components
    wholesale/        # Wholesale-only components
    shared/           # Shared across roles (order timeline, badges)
    customer/         # Public-facing components
  lib/
    supabase/server.ts  # createClient() for server context
    utils.ts            # cn(), formatMAD(), getWholesaleTier()
  types/
    database.ts         # Hand-written DB types (Product, Order, Profile, etc.)
  middleware.ts         # Session refresh
supabase/
  migrations/         # Sequential SQL files: 001_initial_schema.sql … NNN_name.sql
  config.toml         # Supabase CLI config
```

## Patterns

### Data fetching — always server-side
```typescript
// ✅ Server component
const { data } = await supabase.from('products').select('*')

// ❌ Never fetch in useEffect for initial data
```

### Mutations — always server actions
```typescript
// ✅ src/app/actions/products.ts
'use server'
export async function upsertProduct(state, formData) { ... }

// ❌ Never POST to /api routes for mutations
```

### Client components — only for interactivity
Use `'use client'` only when you need: `useState`, `useEffect`, `useRouter`, event handlers, `useActionState`.

### Forms — useActionState pattern
```typescript
const [state, action, isPending] = useActionState(serverAction, initialState)
<form action={action}>
```

### Types — explicit assertions over generics
```typescript
const { data } = await supabase.from('products').select('*') as { data: Product[] | null; error: unknown }
```

## Key utilities
- `formatMAD(n)` — formats number as Moroccan dirham string
- `getWholesaleTier(tiers, qty)` — returns matching wholesale tier
- `cn(...classes)` — Tailwind class merging
